## Bug Summary

In `mainThreadChatSessions.ts`, the `handleSessionModelOverrides` method uses a **global** check (`inProgress.length`) to decide whether to override a session's description with an in-progress description. When *any* session is in progress, it overwrites the description for *all* sessions—including completed ones where `getInProgressSessionDescription()` returns `undefined`, destroying their original description.

## Root Cause

Commit `8c49425799a` ("Fix edge case for in progress session") introduced this bug by refactoring the description logic. The old code had a safe fallback (`description: description || session.description`), but the new code unconditionally assigns `session.description = getInProgressSessionDescription(model)` under a global guard.

## Proposed Fix (High Confidence)

**One file, ~3 lines changed** in `src/vs/workbench/api/browser/mainThreadChatSessions.ts`:

```typescript
// BEFORE (buggy):
const inProgress = this._chatSessionsService.getInProgress();
if (inProgress.length) {
    session.description = this._chatSessionsService.getInProgressSessionDescription(model);
}

// AFTER (fixed):
const desc = this._chatSessionsService.getInProgressSessionDescription(model);
if (desc !== undefined) {
    session.description = desc;
}
```

This removes the faulty global guard and only overwrites the description when there's actually a defined in-progress description for the specific session.

