Now I can clearly see the bug. The issue is at lines 505-508:

```typescript
const inProgress = this._chatSessionsService.getInProgress();
if (inProgress.length) {
    session.description = this._chatSessionsService.getInProgressSessionDescription(model);
}
```

The problem:
1. `getInProgress()` returns all in-progress sessions globally
2. If ANY session is in progress, it enters the `if` block for ALL sessions (even completed ones)
3. `getInProgressSessionDescription(model)` returns `undefined` for completed sessions
4. So `session.description` gets set to `undefined` for completed sessions, losing their original description


5. I should check `localAgentSessionsProvider.ts` since it likely has the same pattern and would need the same fix.

